    "recap_text": "NORTH CHARLESTON, S.C. -\nNorth Florida Baseball fell in its\u00a0midweek game at Charleston Southern, 11-6, at CSU Ballpark on Tuesday.\nNorth Florida's bats were hot early, plating three runs in the first inning and one run in the fourth frame. Sophomore utility player\nSeth Alford\nnotched a one-out double to right field in the top of the first inning. Junior infielder\nMathew Farner\ndrove in Alford with an RBI double to left field to give North Florida a 1-0 advantage.\nRedshirt junior utility player\nJackson Toberman\nhelped give\u00a0North Florida a 2-0 lead in the first inning with an RBI single up the middle. Redshirt sophomore outfielder\nCarter White\ncapped off North Florida's three-run first frame with an RBI base hit to right field.\nFreshman infielder\nJonathan Acosta\nscored on a wild pitch to put UNF ahead, 4-0, in the top of the fourth frame.\nRedshirt junior right-handed pitcher\nWill Ross\nand redshirt sophomore right-handed pitcher\nTyler Kozera\ncombined for 5.0 shutout innings to open the game.\nCharleston Southern responded with two runs in the sixth inning and five runs in the seventh. However, North Florida displayed immense fight down the stretch.\nJunior infielder\nMitchell Collins\ncrossed home on an error in the top of the eighth frame to cut UNF's deficit to 7-5. Farner then delivered his second extra-base hit and second RBI of the game with a double that brought North Florida within one run of Charleston Southern.\nThe Buccaneers plated their final four runs of the game in the eighth frame, bringing the score to its eventual final margin.\nNORTH FLORIDA 6, CHARLESTON SOUTHERN 11\nPitchers of Record\nWin:\nAydan Smith (2-0)\nLoss:\nBrandon Adams\n(1-1)\nLine Scores\nCHARLESTON SOUTHERN\n| 11 R, 15 H, 1 E\nNORTH FLORIDA\n| 6 R, 8 H, 1 E\nStatistical Leaders\nNORTH FLORIDA\nSeth Alford\n| 2-4, 2 R, 1 2B\nMathew Farner\n| 2-5, 2 RBI, 2 2B, 1 R\nCarter White\n| 2-4, 1 RBI, 1 BB\nTyler Kozera\n| 3.0 IP, 0 R, 0 ER, 1 H, 1 K, 0 BB\nCHARLESTON SOUTHERN\nAlex Marot | 3-4, 3 RBI, 1 R, 1 BB\nUP NEXT\nNorth Florida will return to Harmon Stadium from its four-game road stand to host Florida Gulf Coast for a three game series starting Friday, March 20 at 6:05 p.m. ET."
